metadata.title: UK: where people have never used the internet
metadata.description: Share of UK population saying they have never used the internet in 2018, by country/region
metadata.main_insight: In 2018, there was significant variation in the percentage of people who had never used the internet across different regions of the UK, with Northern Ireland having the highest percentage and London the lowest.

datafacts.annotation: Northern Ireland has highest Non-Internet Users
datafacts.reason: Northern Ireland has the highest Non-Internet Users at 12.8
London has the lowest Non-Internet Users at 5.7

datafacts.annotation: Gap between highest and lowest is 7.1000000000000005
datafacts.reason: The difference between the highest value (12.8) and lowest value (5.7) is 7.1000000000000005
The average Non-Internet Users across all Region values is 9.0

datafacts.annotation: Non-Internet Users varies significantly across Region
datafacts.reason: The Non-Internet Users shows considerable variation across different Region values, with a range of 7.1000000000000005
